<li id="cite_note-5"><b><a href="#cite_ref-5" title="">^</a></b> National Association of Corporate Directors (NACD) – Directors Monthly, “Enlightened Boards: Action Beyond Obligation”, Vol. 31Number 12 (2007), Pg 13. <a href="http://www.xceo.net/admin/files/events/Crawford.Directors_Monthly.Dec07_final.pdf" class="external autonumber" title="http://www.xceo.net/admin/files/events/Crawford.Directors_Monthly.Dec07_final.pdf" rel="nofollow">[2]</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-footnote_1-6"><b><a href="#cite_ref-footnote_1_6-0" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://theyrule.net" class="external text" title="http://theyrule.net" rel="nofollow">Theyrule.net</a></li>
<li id="cite_note-7"><b><a href="#cite_ref-7" title="">^</a></b> <a href="http://www.akingump.com/docs/publication/795.pdf" class="external text" title="http://www.akingump.com/docs/publication/795.pdf" rel="nofollow">The Disney Decision of 2005 and the precedent it sets for corporate governance and fiduciary responsibility, Kuckreja, Akin Gump, Aug 2005</a></li>
